latestPosts.caption:
Is your kohl pencil irritating your eyes❓If yes, then you need to watch this video.

Most black pigments in eye makeup come from carbon black, or a version of it. Carbon black is made from the incomplete combustion of petroleum products like coal or coal tar, ethylene, or fuel oil. It is often contaminated with arsenic, lead, mercury, sulfur, and PAH’s 😰

Most women use it every day in their delicate and sensitive eye area. At Ruby’s we developed a simple kohl pencil, that contains NO synthetic chemicals or preservatives and only 100% naturally derived ingredients and pigments 💚

In Frame: Our Founder - Rubeina Karachiwalla
